{
  "skillId": "identify-parts-of-expression",
  "atomType": "R",
  "theory": {
    "intro": "Every algebraic expression is built from **terms**. Each term carries its own sign, and a term with a pronumeral has a **coefficient** (the number multiplying it). A term that is just a number is the **constant term**.",
    "facts": [
      "A **term** is a part of an expression; terms are **separated by addition**.",
      "Treat every subtraction as **adding a negative**, so the sign travels with the term: $3x - 4y$ has terms $3x$ and $-4y$.",
      "The **coefficient** is the number multiplying a pronumeral. In $3x$ it is $3$; in $-9x$ it is $-9$; in $\\frac{x}{3}$ it is $\\frac{1}{3}$.",
      "A term written as just a pronumeral has coefficient $1$: $x$ has coefficient $1$ and $-x$ has coefficient $-1$.",
      "The **constant term** is a term with no pronumeral. If every term has a pronumeral, the constant term is $0$."
    ],
    "steps": [
      "Rewrite subtractions.",
      "Split into terms.",
      "Read coefficient.",
      "Find constant."
    ]
  },
  "practice": {
    "foundation": [
      {
        "question_text": "List all the terms in $4a + 2b + c$.",
        "solution_text": "$4a + 2b + c$\n$4a,\\ 2b,\\ c$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "State the coefficient of $n$ in $17n + 24$.",
        "solution_text": "$17n + 24$\n$17$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Identify the constant term in $2x + 3y + 6$.",
        "solution_text": "$2x + 3y + 6$\n$6$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "State the coefficient of $n$ in $n + 51$.",
        "solution_text": "$n + 51$\n$= 1n + 51$\n$1$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "State the coefficient of $x$ in $\\frac{x}{3}$.",
        "solution_text": "$\\frac{x}{3}$\n$= \\frac{1}{3}x$\n$\\frac{1}{3}$"
      }
    ],
    "development": [
      {
        "question_text": "List all the terms in $3x - 4y + 9$.",
        "solution_text": "$3x - 4y + 9$\n$= 3x + (-4y) + 9$\n$3x,\\ -4y,\\ 9$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "State the coefficient of $a$ in $-2a + 4b + 9$.",
        "solution_text": "$-2a + 4b + 9$\n$-2$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "State the coefficient of $x$ in $18 - 9x$.",
        "solution_text": "$18 - 9x$\n$= 18 + (-9x)$\n$-9$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "State the coefficient of $x$ in $\\frac{3x}{7}$.",
        "solution_text": "$\\frac{3x}{7}$\n$= \\frac{3}{7}x$\n$\\frac{3}{7}$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Identify the constant term in $3x - 11$.",
        "solution_text": "$3x - 11$\n$= 3x + (-11)$\n$-11$"
      }
    ],
    "mastery": [
      {
        "question_text": "Identify the constant term in $7p - 12 + 4q$.",
        "solution_text": "$7p - 12 + 4q$\n$= 7p + (-12) + 4q$\n$-12$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "State the coefficient of $a$ in $3b - \\frac{3a}{7} - 14$.",
        "solution_text": "$3b - \\frac{3a}{7} - 14$\n$= 3b + \\left(-\\frac{3a}{7}\\right) + (-14)$\n$= 3b + \\left(-\\frac{3}{7}\\right)a + (-14)$\n$-\\frac{3}{7}$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "State the coefficient of $x$ in $9 - x$.",
        "solution_text": "$9 - x$\n$= 9 + (-x)$\n$= 9 + (-1)x$\n$-1$"
      }
    ]
  }
